On the second day of my internship, I studied the fundamental principles of the Canny edge detection 
algorithm, which had been assigned by my supervisor as part of the preliminary preparation for the 
project. Since image processing will play a significant role in the development of the virtual piano 
system, understanding the operating principles of this algorithm was considered one of the initial steps
of the project development process.

During the research, I first examined the purpose of edge detection in digital image processing and its 
importance in computer vision applications. I learned that edge detection enables the identification of 
object boundaries by detecting significant intensity changes within an image, allowing objects to be 
distinguished from the background. It was also understood that this information plays an important 
role in applications such as object recognition, motion analysis, and hand gesture detection.

In addition, I investigated the advantages of the Canny algorithm compared to other edge detection 
methods. It was found that the algorithm is widely used in image processing applications because of 
its robustness against noise, its ability to minimize false edge detections, and its high accuracy in 
determining edge locations.

By the end of the day, I had gained a sufficient understanding of the fundamental working principle, 
purpose, and significance of the Canny edge detection algorithm in the field of image processing. The
knowledge acquired through this research is expected to contribute to the development of the image 
processing components of the project in the following stages and to facilitate a better understanding of
potential challenges that may arise during the implementation process.
